# Monorepo Setup - Git Subtrees

This monorepo contains `telecine` (private) and `elements` (public) as git subtrees.

## Structure
- `telecine/` - Private repository (git subtree)
- `elements/` - Public repository (git subtree)
- `scripts/` - Helper scripts for subtree management

## Publishing Changes

Use helper scripts to push to respective repositories:
- `./scripts/push-telecine` - Push telecine subtree to private repo
- `./scripts/push-elements` - Push elements subtree to public repo
- `./scripts/pull-telecine` - Pull telecine updates
- `./scripts/pull-elements` - Pull elements updates

## Important
- Elements commits are PUBLIC - ensure commit messages don't reference telecine internals
- Both repos developed in lock-step (same branch)
- Worktrees contain both directories automatically
- See `.cursor/rules/monorepo-setup.mdc` for detailed documentation

